3629\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hzd1665702710226.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hzd1665702710226.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hzd1665702710226.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hzd1665702710226\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\"> Modeled Entity Interface \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__modeled_entity_interface_316515\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Modeled Entity Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for\n      the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Interface</span> property of a Database Entity. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96356e1_d96357e1_d96358e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Interface</span> property\n         controls how the data is stored in a database, including the maximum number of occurrences,\n         the length of each occurrence, the character set used, and variable-length techniques\n         used.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96359e1_d96360e1_d96361e1\">Entities that reference the Modeled Entity Interface\n         inherit the complete entity interface definition. If the Modeled Entity Interface changes,\n         the change is applied to inheriting entities when they are recompiled.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96362e1_d96363e1_d96364e1\">Modeled Field Interface objects are used during\n         development. They are linked into the modeled entity or component and resolved during\n         compilation.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__topic_d64432e1_d64433e1_d64434e1_d64435e1_d64436e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1029893e68\"> Specialization </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96368e1_d96369e1_d96370e1\">Modeled Entity Interface specializes Development\n            Object in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39047e1_d39048e1_d39049e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96371e1_d96372e1_d96373e1\">It specifies a value for an <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database\n                     Interface</span> property of an entity.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39050e1_d39051e1_d39052e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96374e1_d96375e1_d96376e1\">It has an Entity Interface Library called\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">LIB</code> as parent object.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39053e1_d39054e1_d39055e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96377e1_d96378e1_d96379e1\">It contains no child development objects or code\n                  containers.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39056e1_d39057e1_d39058e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__p_d96380e1_d96381e1_d96382e1\">It has no compiled or generated output.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__topic_d64437e1_d64438e1_d64439e1_d64440e1_d64441e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1029893e111\"> Properties</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39059e1_d39060e1_d39061e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrq1665702585385.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrq1665702585385.html\" title=\"Name of the development object, which uniquely identifies it.\">Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39062e1_d39063e1_d39064e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39065e1_d39066e1_d39067e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"udr1665702710295.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/udr1665702710295.html\" title=\"Character set used for storing the entity in the database.\">Character Set</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39068e1_d39069e1_d39070e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"blo1665702710364.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/blo1665702710364.html\" title=\"Specify the character set used for String fields with the W packing code. If the database does not support Unicode, or it supports only Unicode BMP, use this setting to change its behavior. Valid values are Unicode, BMP, or Use Character Set.\">Wide Character Behavior</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39071e1_d39072e1_d39073e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mcw1665702710436.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mcw1665702710436.html\" title=\"Method used to identify the beginning of an included entities and occurrences using variable length techniques.\">Identification Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39074e1_d39075e1_d39076e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uhg1665702710574.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uhg1665702710574.html\" title=\"ASCII string that marks the beginning of an included entity.\">Entity Identifier</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39077e1_d39078e1_d39079e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"opw1665702710725.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/opw1665702710725.html\" title=\"ASCII string that marks the beginning of the first occurrence of an included entity.\">First Occurrence Identifier</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39080e1_d39081e1_d39082e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xaa1665702710795.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xaa1665702710795.html\" title=\"ASCII string that marks the beginning of all subsequent occurrences of an included entity when using variable-length techniques.\">Next Occurrence Identifier</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39083e1_d39084e1_d39085e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"guc1665702710864.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/guc1665702710864.html\" title=\"Physical size of the entity or included entity, in characters.\">Fixed Length of Entity</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39086e1_d39087e1_d39088e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fwr1665702710934.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fwr1665702710934.html\" title=\"Number of characters allocated to each occurrence of the entity.\">Fixed Length of Occurrence</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hzd1665702710226__li_d39089e1_d39090e1_d39091e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bck1665702654827.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bck1665702654827.html\" title=\"Extended description of the global object.\">Comments</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/enu1665702584272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Interface (Entities)</a><p>This property (also known as the entity interface) determines how the data is mapped to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cpz1704371188325.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Modeled Properties</a><p>Modeled properties are development objects that can be reused in selected properties to enforce consistent patterns for storing, entering, and displaying data. You model properties for the Database Interface, Field Syntax, and Field Layout properties.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613629\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613629\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Modeled Entity Interface Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Modeled Entity Interface A Modeled Entity Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Entity. The Database Interface property controls how the data is stored in a database, including the maximum number of occurrences, the length of each occurrence, the character set used, and variable-length techniques used. Entities that reference the Modeled Entity Interface inherit the complete entity interface definition. If the Modeled Entity Interface changes, the change is applied to inheriting entities when they are recompiled. Modeled Field Interface objects are used during development. They are linked into the modeled entity or component and resolved during compilation. Specialization Modeled Entity Interface specializes Development Object in the following ways: It specifies a value for an Database Interface property of an entity. It has an Entity Interface Library called LIB as parent object. It contains no child development objects or code containers. It has no compiled or generated output. Properties Name Description Character Set Wide Character Behavior Identification Type Entity Identifier First Occurrence Identifier Next Occurrence Identifier Fixed Length of Entity Fixed Length of Occurrence Comments Related Links Database Interface (Entities) This property (also known as the entity interface) determines how the data is mapped to the database. Modeled Properties Modeled properties are development objects that can be reused in selected properties to enforce consistent patterns for storing, entering, and displaying data. You model properties for the Database Interface, Field Syntax, and Field Layout properties. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}